did.unittitle: School of Architecture, Yale University, records concerning admissions and registration

repository.corpname: Yale University. Department of Manuscripts and Archives

did.abstract: The records consist of admission and registration records, correspondence, course schedules and syllabi, programs, and press clippings documenting various activities of the Yale School of Architecture related to student administration and support. Also included are records documenting the 1963 dedication of the School of Architecture building.

odd.head: General note
odd.p: Forms part of Yale Record Group 19-E (YRG 19-E), Records of departments, offices, programs, and projects of the Yale School of Architecture.

acqinfo.head: Immediate Source of Acquisition
acqinfo.p: The records were transferred from the School of Architecture, 2006-2009.

accessrestrict.head: Conditions Governing Access
accessrestrict.p: Access to the materials is restricted. See Collection Contents for details.

userestrict.head: Conditions Governing Use

prefercite.head: Preferred Citation
prefercite.p: School of Architecture, Yale University, Records Concerning Admissions and Registration (RU 1012). Manuscripts and Archives, Yale University Library.

processinfo.head: Processing Information
processinfo.p: Yale University records are arranged and described at the accession level by the creating office. The University Archives creates collection level descriptive records, but typically does no further arrangement and description at the accession level.

scopecontent.head: Scope and Contents
scopecontent.p: The records consist of admission and registration records, correspondence, course schedules and syllabi, programs, and press clippings documenting various activities of the Yale School of Architecture related to student administration and support. Also included are records documenting the 1963 dedication of the School of Architecture building.

arrangement.head: Arrangement
arrangement.p: The records are arranged by accession.
